You should set `&lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;` for the Jib plugin in all modules (including the root `pom.xml`) but `spring-app`.

Just in case, I am talking about skipping `jib-maven-plugin`. Skipping `spring-boot-maven-plugin` as you did won&#39;t prevent from Jib from running, since it&#39;s just a different plugin.

```xml
      &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.cloud.tools&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;jib-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
          &lt;!-- we don&#39;t want jib to execute on this module --&gt;
          &lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
      &lt;/plugin&gt;
```

The Jib repository hosts a [multi-module example project](https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/jib/tree/master/examples/multi-module) with this setup. For example, the root `pom.xml` and the `shared-library` sub-module skip the Jib plugin.

