# Solution

#### Application
A webflux application, with an endpoint receiving multipart data, including a file. The application is based on Spring boot 3.1.5


### Goal
Find the ```Path``` of the file created on the filesystem, to use it afterward


### Original code

```java
@PostMapping(value = &quot;/upload&quot;, consumes = MediaType.MULTIPART_FORM_DATA_VALUE)
public Mono&lt;Void&gt; upload(@RequestParam String token, @RequestPart Mono&lt;FilePart&gt; file) {
	// Here, there is no way to access to the Path of the file argument once 
	// received &amp; created on the filesystem by Spring
	// Only solution is to create a copy with the FilePart#transferTo() method
}
```


## Actual Solution

Spring 6.x introduces ```PartEvent``` ([documentation][1]) that allows receiving files from a multipart request by chunk, preventing Spring from creating the whole file on the filesystem by itself. Instead, it is our code that creates the file on the filesystem, and thus we have full control on the Path and we reach our goal to have only one copy of the file on the filesystem.

#### Code

```java
// Note: parts of the code are omitted for brevity
// The class PartEvent has a complete code example in its javadoc
@PostMapping(value = &quot;/upload&quot;, consumes = MediaType.MULTIPART_FORM_DATA_VALUE)
public Mono&lt;Void&gt; upload2(@RequestParam String token, @RequestBody Flux&lt;PartEvent&gt; allPartsEvents) {

	return allPartsEvents.windowUntil(PartEvent::isLast)
		.concatMap(p -&gt; p.switchOnFirst((signal, partEvents) -&gt; {
			PartEvent event = signal.get();
			if (event instanceof FilePartEvent fileEvent) {
				// Here we create the file on the filesystem
				return FileUtils.createTempFile(fileEvent.filename())
					.flatMap(path -&gt;
						// And here we write in the file following the Flux&lt;PartEvent&gt; we are receiving
						DataBufferUtils.write(partEvents.map(PartEvent::content), path,
							StandardOpenOption.CREATE));
			}

			return Mono.empty();
		})).then();
}
```


  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/http/codec/multipart/PartEvent.html

